1
00:00:01,459 --> 00:00:07,716
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:09,884 --> 00:00:14,389
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:18,768 --> 00:00:20,895
- [Audrey] <i>Is she as pretty as me?</i>
- [Gavin blows raspberry]

4
00:00:20,979 --> 00:00:23,690
[Audrey] <i>I also met someone,</i>
<i>a few years ago.</i>

5
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:26,025
- <i>I was not able to introduce him to Dad.</i>
- [Gavin, in English] <i>What happened?</i>

6
00:00:26,109 --> 00:00:28,194
[both grunt]

7
00:00:28,278 --> 00:00:29,779
I never saw him again.

8
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:31,948
[Ibyang] <i>What is Master busy with?</i>

9
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:33,283
Is it still the rooster?

10
00:00:33,366 --> 00:00:36,161
It seems like I know where
the rooster you are looking for is.

11
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:38,246
[Ame] <i>Draco. That is the name.</i>

12
00:00:38,329 --> 00:00:39,581
Where did you hear that?

13
00:00:39,664 --> 00:00:42,500
[man 1, in English] <i>Chipper,</i>
<i>as in Chipper Arenas?</i>

14
00:00:42,584 --> 00:00:44,461
You are now the official
makeup artist from now on.

15
00:00:44,544 --> 00:00:45,837
- Is that okay?
- Really?!

16
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:47,005
[elated shrieking]

17
00:00:47,088 --> 00:00:48,882
Thank you so much!

18
00:00:48,965 --> 00:00:50,216
[Tonet] <i>Can I talk to you?</i>

19
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:52,719
[Ame] <i>Actually, I also</i>
<i>want to talk to you.</i>

20
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:54,471
- Do you like Atoy?
- You have a crush on Atoy.

21
00:00:54,554 --> 00:00:55,597
PREVIOUSLY

22
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:57,057
[gasps]

23
00:00:57,140 --> 00:01:00,643
[Atoy, in English] <i>Hello,</i>
<i>this is, uh, Mr. Arenas.</i>

24
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:03,521
[in English] <i>I would like to cancel,</i>
<i>uh, my booking.</i>

25
00:01:03,605 --> 00:01:05,857
<i>The child changed her mind.</i>

26
00:01:06,608 --> 00:01:08,610
<i>She doesn’t want to see a magician.</i>

27
00:01:09,611 --> 00:01:10,820
[woman on phone] <i>Noted, sir.</i>

28
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:13,740
[in English] Okay, maybe next time.

29
00:01:13,823 --> 00:01:16,367
[woman on phone, in English]
<i>Okay, Mr. Arenas, have a good day.</i>

30
00:01:16,451 --> 00:01:17,744
What are you saying?

31
00:01:17,827 --> 00:01:19,162
I do not have a crush on Atoy.

32
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:21,456
And I am still young.
I do not want a boyfriend yet.

33
00:01:21,539 --> 00:01:23,291
- Career first!
- [playful music playing]

34
00:01:23,374 --> 00:01:25,376
Just a crush and already a boyfriend?

35
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:26,336
You are something else!

36
00:01:26,419 --> 00:01:27,545
What about you?

37
00:01:27,629 --> 00:01:29,214
Why? Admit it!

38
00:01:30,089 --> 00:01:30,965
I can see it.

39
00:01:31,049 --> 00:01:33,593
The way you look at Atoy is different.

40
00:01:33,676 --> 00:01:37,096
And you are very clingy with him.

41
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:40,850
Oh, just being friendly,
and that is already clingy?

42
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:42,977
For your information…

43
00:01:43,061 --> 00:01:45,063
I do not like Atoy.

44
00:01:45,146 --> 00:01:46,815
I just really have a big debt of gratitude

45
00:01:46,898 --> 00:01:51,319
because he saved my life,
and he is letting Ibyang and me stay here!

46
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:53,613
Oh, then this.

47
00:01:53,696 --> 00:01:55,573
If you really do not like Atoy,

48
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:57,784
why are you asking
if I have a crush on him?

49
00:01:57,867 --> 00:01:59,494
Are you a gossiper? Huh, huh, huh?!

50
00:01:59,577 --> 00:02:01,830
Of course, I am concerned about Atoy.

51
00:02:01,913 --> 00:02:03,248
- [Tonet shrieks]
- What if your intentions

52
00:02:03,331 --> 00:02:04,958
- toward him are not good!
- [offende chuckle]

53
00:02:05,041 --> 00:02:07,794
[scoffs] That is really too much!

54
00:02:07,877 --> 00:02:09,129
And you?

55
00:02:10,046 --> 00:02:15,260
Why are you interested in knowing
if I have a crush on him?

56
00:02:17,095 --> 00:02:19,973
- Oh, so?
- [stammering] Oh, why? Oh?

57
00:02:20,056 --> 00:02:21,266
- He is my boss.
- Oh?

58
00:02:21,349 --> 00:02:24,394
Naturally, I would be concerned!

59
00:02:24,477 --> 00:02:26,020
My boss.

60
00:02:26,104 --> 00:02:27,438
Boss? Hmm?

61
00:02:27,522 --> 00:02:30,733
[playful music continues]

62
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:32,443
Boss? [mutters]

63
00:02:34,112 --> 00:02:37,699
[suave music playing]

64
00:02:37,782 --> 00:02:39,159
[sewing machine whirring]

65
00:02:39,242 --> 00:02:40,118
[swishing]

66
00:02:40,201 --> 00:02:41,077
[snipping]

67
00:02:42,203 --> 00:02:43,621
[sewing machine whirring]

68
00:02:43,705 --> 00:02:45,999
[sewing machine whirring]

69
00:02:46,082 --> 00:02:46,791
[gun cocks]

70
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:49,377
[gun firing]

71
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:50,503
[clicking]

72
00:02:51,754 --> 00:02:53,089
[snips]

73
00:02:54,299 --> 00:02:56,509
[electronic blipping]

74
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:02,098
It is because you…

75
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:04,267
[indistinct chatter]

76
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:07,353
- Oh, go, go, Karla!
- Go, go, take your shot!

77
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:09,522
- Hey, hey!
- Go, go, do your layup!

78
00:03:09,606 --> 00:03:10,440
You did not chase it.

79
00:03:10,523 --> 00:03:11,941
- Whoo!
- Huh?

80
00:03:12,025 --> 00:03:13,401
Is that what you call defense, T-Bak?

81
00:03:13,484 --> 00:03:15,778
- Hmm!
- I did not even break a sweat.

82
00:03:16,487 --> 00:03:18,489
So, one more game?

83
00:03:18,573 --> 00:03:20,283
- One more! Can you still handle it?
- I am done.

84
00:03:20,366 --> 00:03:21,200
This one does not even know how to play!

85
00:03:21,284 --> 00:03:22,702
It feels unfair.
My teammate cannot keep up.

86
00:03:22,785 --> 00:03:23,870
- Me, me?
- Yes!

87
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:24,787
We will join!

88
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:25,914
[in English] Three-on-three.

89
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:29,459
I do not want you as my teammate.

90
00:03:29,542 --> 00:03:30,501
[in English] Game!

91
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:32,462
- Jason is yours.
- G!

92
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:35,089
Guard me. Let us see
if you can still score on me.

93
00:03:35,173 --> 00:03:36,424
- Oh!
- In your dreams!

94
00:03:36,507 --> 00:03:38,301
Pass it out. I am giving you
a handicap already.

95
00:03:38,384 --> 00:03:39,802
- [in English] Okay!
- [chuckles]

96
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:41,346
Oh, come on, game!

97
00:03:41,429 --> 00:03:44,015
[in English] Game! Let's go!

98
00:03:44,098 --> 00:03:45,433
Come here!

99
00:03:45,516 --> 00:03:46,976
- [energetic music playing]
- Ha!

100
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,519
- Ha!
- Oh, are you ready to play?

101
00:03:48,603 --> 00:03:49,520
G!

102
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:51,189
There are so many
other places to hang out.

103
00:03:51,272 --> 00:03:52,523
Why are you here in Tabang Lupa?

104
00:03:53,483 --> 00:03:54,442
Well, because of Jason.

105
00:03:54,525 --> 00:03:56,611
He likes your friend,
so he always invites us here.

106
00:03:57,528 --> 00:03:58,529
[grunts]

107
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:01,991
Jason!

108
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,701
Did Tonet not already say she is taken?

109
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:05,328
He said he is willing to wait.

110
00:04:08,081 --> 00:04:14,128
- [T-Bak] Whoa!
- [energetic music continues]

111
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:17,423
[in English] Tonet?
Will she be here later?

112
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:19,092
She is not fond of basketball.

113
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:20,885
And she is busy at the shop, right?

114
00:04:20,969 --> 00:04:23,346
Have clothes sewn there
if you want to see her.

115
00:04:25,890 --> 00:04:27,141
[in English] Oh, game.

116
00:04:28,726 --> 00:04:30,353
[energetic music continues]

117
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:31,771
[Jason] Ball, ball, ball!

118
00:04:31,854 --> 00:04:33,523
- Oh!
- [T-Bak] Whoa!

119
00:04:33,606 --> 00:04:34,691
[T-Bak] Whoa!

120
00:04:34,774 --> 00:04:38,486
[T-bak whooping]

121
00:04:40,196 --> 00:04:43,741
[energetic music continues]

122
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:45,451
[Atoy] Come here.

123
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:47,412
[Atoy] Hmm.

124
00:04:48,579 --> 00:04:52,458
[mischievous music playing]

125
00:04:52,542 --> 00:04:54,460
- Oh.
- [chuckles]

126
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:55,586
- Are you okay?
- [chuckles]

127
00:04:56,212 --> 00:04:57,672
[in English] Thank you, Atoy.

128
00:04:57,755 --> 00:04:59,549
You are really kind to me.

129
00:04:59,632 --> 00:05:01,426
You even thought of that?

130
00:05:01,509 --> 00:05:02,552
It was nothing.

131
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:05,430
- [Atoy] It was a small thing. [chuckles]
- [Ame chuckles]

132
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:07,724
At least you can open it now.

133
00:05:07,807 --> 00:05:08,891
Exactly.

134
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:11,060
Ah…

135
00:05:11,978 --> 00:05:13,438
Tonet.

136
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:15,189
Are you still game to help me

137
00:05:15,773 --> 00:05:18,693
and be my makeup artist?

138
00:05:19,277 --> 00:05:20,403
Of course!

139
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:21,529
You can always count on me!

140
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:23,990
[in English] Anything and everything.

141
00:05:24,615 --> 00:05:27,702
Too many words, around 20.

142
00:05:28,494 --> 00:05:29,746
[Atoy] I have an appointment on Saturday.

143
00:05:30,788 --> 00:05:33,875
I really need your help.
I need your expertise.

144
00:05:33,958 --> 00:05:35,335
No problem, Atoy! [scoffs]

145
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:37,837
[in English] Anything
and everything for you.

146
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:38,755
You have a strong pull with me.

147
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:41,340
[Ame] Ah, Atoy,
maybe you also need my help.

148
00:05:41,424 --> 00:05:42,508
Just say the word.

149
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:44,010
[Atoy] Uh…

150
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:46,262
You know, actually,

151
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:48,431
I also need your help.

152
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:50,016
[in English] Yes, Atoy.

153
00:05:50,099 --> 00:05:51,017
Whatever it is, I am game.

154
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:51,934
- [Atoy] Anything?
- Mm-hmm.

155
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:52,977
[Atoy] No, uh…

156
00:05:53,644 --> 00:05:55,980
I am just really shy to ask you but…

157
00:05:57,482 --> 00:06:00,109
I really need you
this Saturday too. As in…

158
00:06:00,735 --> 00:06:03,071
Perfect, yes! Can you do it?

159
00:06:03,154 --> 00:06:05,198
Yes, game!

160
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:06,616
- [in English] Game?
- [Ame] Mm-hmm.

161
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:09,619
[mischievous music continues]

162
00:06:10,119 --> 00:06:11,913
Oh, Master…

163
00:06:11,996 --> 00:06:13,289
Where are we going now?

164
00:06:13,372 --> 00:06:14,290
Going out?

165
00:06:14,373 --> 00:06:16,167
- Oh, nowhere.
- [Ibyang] Yes.

166
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:18,419
Children are not allowed
to where I am going!

167
00:06:19,003 --> 00:06:20,046
Um…

168
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:22,048
No kids allowed?

169
00:06:22,131 --> 00:06:23,591
[Atoy] Yes, no kids allowed.

170
00:06:23,674 --> 00:06:26,010
Especially those who are…
the annoying ones.

171
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:27,887
And those who keep asking questions.

172
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:28,846
[Tonet] Oh, that is you.

173
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:30,890
- So where are you going?
- Like that, like that!

174
00:06:30,973 --> 00:06:32,475
The ones who keep asking like that!

175
00:06:32,558 --> 00:06:33,976
You are not allowed there.

176
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:35,144
Oh, asking questions?

177
00:06:35,228 --> 00:06:37,146
So, oh, asking questions.

178
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,564
[Tonet chuckles]

179
00:06:39,148 --> 00:06:40,399
What is this for?

180
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:41,567
[in English] Wedding gown?

181
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:44,028
Because we need to wear costumes

182
00:06:44,112 --> 00:06:46,364
at the next place we are going to.

183
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:48,533
- Hmm.
- Is that okay with you?

184
00:06:48,616 --> 00:06:50,243
Of course, that is fine.

185
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:57,583
- [dreamy music playing]
- Here.

186
00:06:58,417 --> 00:07:00,086
[giggles] Smells good!

187
00:07:02,922 --> 00:07:04,215
Ah…

188
00:07:04,298 --> 00:07:06,134
[clears throat] Ame?

189
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:09,178
[in English] Oh, sorry, sorry.

190
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:14,600
[dreamy music continues]

191
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,565
One more.

192
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:22,358
This.

193
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:23,651
[in English] Neckline.

194
00:07:26,737 --> 00:07:27,905
Hmm.

195
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:31,200
[dreamy music continues]

196
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:32,743
[chuckles]

197
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:33,744
Uh-huh.

198
00:07:35,204 --> 00:07:37,457
I was counting your moles.

199
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:39,000
There, I lost count because of that.

200
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:41,085
I can no longer tell
if it is lucky or unlucky.

201
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:43,463
- Really?
- How many did you see?

202
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:45,465
I lost count.

203
00:07:46,215 --> 00:07:47,383
You really are something.

204
00:07:48,092 --> 00:07:51,679
[mumbles] I ended up losing
the number I was supposed to write.

205
00:07:51,762 --> 00:07:56,350
["Mamang Sastre" playing]

206
00:08:24,545 --> 00:08:26,506
Just text me when you need a retouch.

207
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:29,091
Or if you need company.

208
00:08:29,175 --> 00:08:31,093
[Ame] What, do you know how to do magic?

209
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:33,513
I made you cute. Is that magic?

210
00:08:33,596 --> 00:08:35,681
[Atoy] Psst! Hey, hey, enough.
Stop teasing each other.

211
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:37,850
Karla, be ready.

212
00:08:37,934 --> 00:08:39,644
You need to be ready,
so that when we come out,

213
00:08:39,727 --> 00:08:41,229
you can pick us up immediately.

214
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:42,522
Copy that, bro!

215
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:44,148
[Atoy] So, Ame, game?

216
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:45,733
[Ame, in English] Game!

217
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:47,443
[grunts]

218
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,445
[playful music playing]

219
00:08:51,072 --> 00:08:52,114
[Ame] Is that enough?

220
00:08:52,990 --> 00:08:54,534
[Mercado] Our man already has a lead

221
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:56,410
on the rooster you asked to be found.

222
00:08:58,996 --> 00:09:01,332
That is good news, Colonel.

223
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,127
[in English] Did I get
your rank right, Colonel?

224
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:06,295
[chuckles]

225
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:08,214
That is no longer important.

226
00:09:09,006 --> 00:09:10,466
I have been retired for a long time.

227
00:09:11,384 --> 00:09:15,179
I only do this for people who need help.

228
00:09:15,263 --> 00:09:18,224
- And of course, those who can pay.
- [Dmitri sighs]

229
00:09:18,307 --> 00:09:19,225
Of course.

230
00:09:20,601 --> 00:09:22,353
[in English] Any amount for my Draco.

231
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:24,397
[in English] You know what, Colonel?

232
00:09:25,189 --> 00:09:27,024
[in English] Draco is my best fighter.

233
00:09:28,025 --> 00:09:29,986
That is why I was forced to come home,

234
00:09:30,486 --> 00:09:32,446
to cut short my vacation,

235
00:09:33,072 --> 00:09:34,907
when I learned that it was stolen.

236
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:38,452
By the way, how did your tracker find it?

237
00:09:39,078 --> 00:09:40,746
[scoffs, inhales]

238
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:41,956
[in English] It is a trade secret.

239
00:09:43,499 --> 00:09:44,709
But rest assured…

240
00:09:45,293 --> 00:09:47,753
my man has never failed.

241
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:51,507
[in English] He will get your Draco,
whatever the cost.

242
00:09:52,091 --> 00:09:54,343
[pensive music playing]

243
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:56,429
[crowd applauding]

244
00:09:56,512 --> 00:09:59,056
Are you excited, kids?

245
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,308
[kids] Yes!

246
00:10:00,391 --> 00:10:02,518
Is Maya excited?

247
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:03,894
[in English] Yes!

248
00:10:03,978 --> 00:10:07,940
[in English] All right!
Without further ado, here they are!

249
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:10,276
[in English] Maya’s special guests.

250
00:10:10,359 --> 00:10:14,614
[in English] The Amazing Tomtom
and Tintin!

251
00:10:14,697 --> 00:10:18,075
- [crowd applauding]
- [mystical music playing]

252
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:20,536
[cheerful music playing]

253
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:23,414
[kids cheering]

254
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:24,874
[in English] Hi, kids!

255
00:10:24,957 --> 00:10:26,000
- [boy] Hi!
- [Atoy chuckles]

256
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:27,668
[Ame] Hi!

257
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:28,586
Whoo!

258
00:10:28,669 --> 00:10:29,962
[chuckles]

259
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:32,715
[Martina, in English]
Everything has to be perfect.

260
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:33,716
[in English] Okay?

261
00:10:33,799 --> 00:10:36,052
I do not want my sister-in-law
to criticize me

262
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:37,803
just because of a crooked painting
or mismatched throw pillows.

263
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:39,430
- [in English] Do you understand?
- [in English] Yes, ma'am.

264
00:10:39,513 --> 00:10:40,890
[Audrey clears throat]

265
00:10:40,973 --> 00:10:43,309
So, I will just come back later

266
00:10:43,392 --> 00:10:47,480
when your house is perfect, Sis Martina?

267
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:49,357
[sinister music playing]

268
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,525
[in English] Audrey, my dear.

269
00:10:52,318 --> 00:10:53,527
[in English] Do you need anything?

270
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:56,614
[in English] Peace of mind might be nice.

271
00:10:56,697 --> 00:10:59,200
But I doubt you have that.

272
00:10:59,992 --> 00:11:01,952
Especially since I am here
right in front of you.

273
00:11:03,996 --> 00:11:05,748
There is no one else here,
so let us not pretend.

274
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:07,041
Is that okay?

275
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:10,836
You yourself said
that your life is already in the US.

276
00:11:12,129 --> 00:11:13,214
Why did you come back here?

277
00:11:14,715 --> 00:11:15,800
Again and again?

278
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:18,260
I already told you.

279
00:11:18,969 --> 00:11:20,388
Dad forced me.

280
00:11:21,305 --> 00:11:22,306
[in English] I know you.

281
00:11:24,141 --> 00:11:26,477
You cannot be easily forced
if you do not want to.

282
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,729
[in English] So, tell me the truth.

283
00:11:28,813 --> 00:11:30,022
[in English] Why are you here?

284
00:11:30,815 --> 00:11:32,733
Are you planning to take
the company from Red?

285
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:36,821
If what Dad heard is true,

286
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:39,448
that Brother mismanaged the company,

287
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:42,701
then I have nothing to take away from him.

288
00:11:43,494 --> 00:11:46,539
[sinister music continues]

289
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:50,000
[in English] Our trucking company
is doing great.

290
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:52,545
[in English] We are doing great.

291
00:11:52,628 --> 00:11:54,422
We do not need your interference.

292
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:56,799
I am not interfering, Sis Martina.

293
00:11:57,675 --> 00:12:01,053
[in English] The company is just
as much mine as it is Brother Red’s.

294
00:12:01,137 --> 00:12:03,597
You asked me if I would stay here long.

295
00:12:04,181 --> 00:12:05,224
[in English] And it really all depends.

296
00:12:06,183 --> 00:12:09,103
If Dad sees that Brother
is being led astray

297
00:12:09,186 --> 00:12:13,607
because of the wrong people
whispering to him,

298
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:17,194
then I guess we will be seeing
a lot more of each other.

299
00:12:17,278 --> 00:12:23,200
[tense music playing]

300
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:33,294
This tracker you are talking about…

301
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:35,421
He used to be your man, right?

302
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:37,089
[scoffs, inhales]

303
00:12:37,173 --> 00:12:39,884
What is important is that
he completes the mission.

304
00:12:40,509 --> 00:12:44,138
I am sure he will recover
your prized game cock.

305
00:12:44,221 --> 00:12:46,015
[in English] Then he must be really good.

306
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:49,518
[in English] Let us just say
he is the best in the business.

307
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:53,397
[in English] You know what, Colonel?
I would like to meet him.

308
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:54,773
[scoffs]

309
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:57,568
[in English] Maybe someday.

310
00:12:58,277 --> 00:13:03,115
[sinister music playing]

311
00:13:06,285 --> 00:13:08,120
[clacks]

312
00:13:08,871 --> 00:13:10,289
[music intensifies, concludes]

313
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:12,958
- [whimsical music playing]
- [Maya] Wow!

314
00:13:15,127 --> 00:13:16,462
[Atoy] Oh.

315
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:17,838
- [whimsical music continues]
- [muttering]

316
00:13:18,756 --> 00:13:20,132
- [Atoy] Oh.
- [chuckles]

317
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:22,843
[whimsical music continues]

318
00:13:26,263 --> 00:13:30,518
[whimsical music continues]

319
00:13:30,601 --> 00:13:31,435
‪[magical twinkling]

320
00:13:33,187 --> 00:13:34,688
‪[whimsical music playing]

321
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:36,440
[kids cheering]

322
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:38,609
[cheering]

323
00:13:38,692 --> 00:13:43,155
[kids applauding, cheering]

324
00:13:47,243 --> 00:13:49,161
- Hmm?
- [kids laughing]

325
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:50,204
[Atoy] Psst!

326
00:13:51,997 --> 00:13:53,415
Not really.

327
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:55,918
[kids laughing]

328
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:58,837
[kids applauding]

329
00:13:58,921 --> 00:14:00,214
[Ame and Atoy chuckle]

330
00:14:02,591 --> 00:14:05,177
[kids cheering]

331
00:14:05,261 --> 00:14:07,054
Looks like you are a hit with the kids.

332
00:14:07,137 --> 00:14:08,180
[guffaws]

333
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:11,392
Try having an Ibyang,
who is extremely naughty,

334
00:14:11,475 --> 00:14:14,979
let us see if you would
not learn to entertain kids too.

335
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:18,107
[kids cheering]

336
00:14:19,316 --> 00:14:21,277
This is my chance to slip away.

337
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,736
- You are on your own.
- [kids chuckle]

338
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:23,737
Copy that.

339
00:14:23,821 --> 00:14:25,030
‪[applauding, cheering]

340
00:14:26,574 --> 00:14:27,408
Whoa!

341
00:14:27,491 --> 00:14:28,993
- [farts]
- Oh, oh.

342
00:14:29,076 --> 00:14:30,244
Oh? Tomtom!

343
00:14:30,327 --> 00:14:32,037
- What is happening to you?!
- [Atoy gasps]

344
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:33,205
- I am pooping!
- [Ame shrieks]

345
00:14:33,289 --> 00:14:35,374
- I am Tomtom-ing!
- [Ame] Oh, no!

346
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:36,709
[kids laughing]

347
00:14:36,792 --> 00:14:39,086
Oh, no, not here! No,
uh, uh, not here, not here!

348
00:14:39,169 --> 00:14:40,421
[stammering]

349
00:14:40,504 --> 00:14:41,714
There!

350
00:14:41,797 --> 00:14:43,716
[Atoy] But how? This is about to explode!

351
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:45,509
- [making fart sound]
- [Ame] W, wait! Oh!

352
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:47,052
There, there, there! At the back!

353
00:14:47,136 --> 00:14:48,846
- There! To the back, hurry!
- [gasps]

354
00:14:48,929 --> 00:14:50,389
Huh? Huh? Okay!

355
00:14:50,472 --> 00:14:52,391
- [kids laughing]
- [Atoy panting]

356
00:14:53,225 --> 00:14:54,768
Miss, where is the restroom here?

357
00:14:56,061 --> 00:14:57,688
There, I thought
it was just a joke earlier!

358
00:14:57,771 --> 00:14:58,981
Come on! It is about to explode!

359
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:00,232
Where is the restroom here? Where?

360
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:03,402
- At the end, to the right.
- At the end?

361
00:15:03,485 --> 00:15:04,570
- To the right?
- Brother--

362
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,113
- Oh, thank you.
- [giggling]

363
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:08,365
Thank you for the invitation.

364
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:10,367
[Atoy] <i>Sorry because my boss</i>
<i>will make me pay for this.</i>

365
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:11,785
[Atoy chuckles]

366
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:13,537
‪Mmm…

367
00:15:13,787 --> 00:15:19,209
Okay, kids, while Tomtom
is doing number one and number two,

368
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:22,421
would you like me
to do magic for you first?

369
00:15:22,504 --> 00:15:25,549
- [kids] Yes!
- [kids applauding]

370
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:32,514
There.

371
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:33,641
Thank you, sir.

372
00:15:34,141 --> 00:15:35,100
Botchog!

373
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:36,852
Boss Chipper?

374
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:37,937
He already needs to do a fitting.

375
00:15:38,020 --> 00:15:38,896
He is inside.

376
00:15:38,979 --> 00:15:39,939
Oh!

377
00:15:41,148 --> 00:15:43,400
Looks like there are
many cars parked outside.

378
00:15:43,484 --> 00:15:45,819
- What is going on?
- Birthday party of my boss’s child.

379
00:15:46,403 --> 00:15:48,405
Is it Maya’s birthday today?!

380
00:15:49,198 --> 00:15:50,866
Oh, no, I was not invited.

381
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:53,035
You want to be invited
to a children’s party?

382
00:15:53,118 --> 00:15:54,411
Of course!

383
00:15:54,495 --> 00:15:57,081
The food there is delicious.
I want free food!

384
00:15:57,164 --> 00:15:58,457
And I want to watch a clown.

385
00:15:58,540 --> 00:15:59,917
That was my favorite when I was a kid.

386
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,127
[scoffs] So, inside? He is inside?

387
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:04,338
- Inside!
- I will look inside.

388
00:16:04,421 --> 00:16:05,255
All right.

389
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:07,007
Ah…

390
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:09,468
[speaks in Visayan language]

391
00:16:10,761 --> 00:16:14,556
[speaks in Visayan language]

392
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,183
[gasps]

393
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:17,142
My God!

394
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:18,769
Who would you even say that to?

395
00:16:18,852 --> 00:16:20,270
No one.

396
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:22,481
Just a reserve in case someone mocks me.

397
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:25,317
Fine then, what other
Bisaya insults do you have?

398
00:16:25,401 --> 00:16:26,860
Wait, a moment.

399
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:28,654
[speaks in Visayan language]

400
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:31,073
[mischievous music playing]

401
00:16:31,156 --> 00:16:32,574
To the party.

402
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:33,659
A happy birthday party.

403
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:36,370
Hey, that looks like Emerson.

404
00:16:36,453 --> 00:16:37,287
No way.

405
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:39,832
Oh, he got inside.

406
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:42,001
Maybe it just looks like him.

407
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:44,753
What a coincidence
that Emerson is also here.

408
00:16:45,587 --> 00:16:46,797
Well…

409
00:16:47,756 --> 00:16:49,341
- [clatters]
- Oh! What was that?

410
00:16:49,425 --> 00:16:50,509
[Tonet] What is that?

411
00:16:50,592 --> 00:16:51,719
[Tonet] What was that?

412
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:53,345
Maybe just a rat.

413
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:55,472
This has been staying
in the garage for a long time.

414
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:57,975
[stammers] Oh no, a rat!

415
00:16:58,058 --> 00:16:59,476
- Kill it, Karla!
- [Karla] Hey.

416
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:00,811
- Kill it! I cannot do it!
- Shh!

417
00:17:00,894 --> 00:17:01,729
I will die, Karla!

418
00:17:01,812 --> 00:17:03,063
- Kill it!
- [shushes]

419
00:17:03,147 --> 00:17:05,149
- You are so brutal! Shh!
- [panting]

420
00:17:05,232 --> 00:17:06,650
Sis! Kill it right away?

421
00:17:06,734 --> 00:17:08,235
You can just drive it out of the van.

422
00:17:08,318 --> 00:17:10,446
Then let it out. Hurry.

423
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:11,905
If that goes to the front…

424
00:17:11,989 --> 00:17:13,574
Hurry, get it!

425
00:17:13,657 --> 00:17:15,451
That will really go to the front.

426
00:17:15,534 --> 00:17:16,994
- Bah!
- [exclaims]

427
00:17:17,077 --> 00:17:18,996
- My God!
- [Karla] Ibyang?

428
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:20,581
[in English] The one and only!

429
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:26,462
[in English] I am here at the golf course.

430
00:17:26,545 --> 00:17:27,880
How are things at the house?

431
00:17:27,963 --> 00:17:30,507
Sister Martina is too defensive.

432
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:32,468
Maybe it is really needed
that someone watches

433
00:17:32,551 --> 00:17:35,012
over Brother in running the company.

434
00:17:35,095 --> 00:17:37,556
[in English] That is exactly why
I need you here.

435
00:17:37,639 --> 00:17:39,266
But, Dad,

436
00:17:39,349 --> 00:17:42,853
you know that someone
is waiting for me in the States.

437
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:46,315
But maybe you can give me
some consideration here.

438
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:49,276
[Dmitri on phone, in English]
<i>Okay, listen.</i>

439
00:17:49,359 --> 00:17:52,529
[in English] Let us just have lunch
and talk about your plans.

440
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:54,406
I will just finish these nine holes.

441
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:56,116
[Dmitri, in English]
<i>I am playing with an old buddy.</i>

442
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,451
[in English] Oh, I remember.

443
00:17:57,951 --> 00:18:00,662
The one who will help you
find your rooster.

444
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:03,040
[in English] The real reason
why you are here.

445
00:18:03,123 --> 00:18:05,334
Well, actually, there is good news.

446
00:18:05,417 --> 00:18:09,713
Master Cutter is close to finding Draco.

447
00:18:09,797 --> 00:18:11,507
[in English] Master Cutter?

448
00:18:13,008 --> 00:18:15,594
[in English] You mean like… a barber?

449
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:17,679
[in English] A tailor.

450
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,557
[chuckles] No, no, no, no.

451
00:18:20,641 --> 00:18:22,309
[in English] He is a tracker.

452
00:18:22,392 --> 00:18:26,480
[in English] He can find anything
or anyone on this earth.

453
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:29,441
- [in English] Anything?
- [Dmitri, in English] <i>Why?</i>

454
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:31,610
Do you want to find someone?

455
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:33,153
[in English] Maybe.

456
00:18:33,987 --> 00:18:35,239
[Dmitri on phone] <i>What do you mean maybe?</i>

457
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:37,574
[in English] <i>Do you have someone in mind?</i>

458
00:18:38,158 --> 00:18:39,159
[in English] Yeah.

459
00:18:40,452 --> 00:18:41,995
[in English] Someone from my past.

460
00:18:42,079 --> 00:18:45,916
[tense music playing]

461
00:18:50,712 --> 00:18:52,256
[whimsical music playing]

462
00:18:55,342 --> 00:18:56,802
Okay.

463
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:58,512
The roosters are here.

464
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:03,058
- Hmm.
- [rooster crowing]

465
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:04,726
Where are you, Draco?

466
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:06,687
Draco, Draco.

467
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,691
These look like slaughter roosters.

468
00:19:10,774 --> 00:19:13,485
- [rooster crowing]
- [whimsical music continues]

469
00:19:20,909 --> 00:19:21,910
Ah!

470
00:19:22,953 --> 00:19:24,454
This looks like it.

471
00:19:24,538 --> 00:19:26,874
[whimsical music continues]

472
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:37,384
Bingo!

473
00:19:37,467 --> 00:19:43,056
[thrilling music playing]

474
00:19:43,140 --> 00:19:44,808
It really is Draco!

475
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:51,607
I will bring you back to your owner.

476
00:19:53,859 --> 00:19:55,569
Go back inside!

477
00:19:55,652 --> 00:19:58,447
If you are seen by Brother Atoy,
you will really be in trouble!

478
00:19:59,781 --> 00:20:02,492
- He will spank you!
- [Ibyang] Hmm?

479
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:07,122
I will not be spanked by Master Grumpy
because he loves me!

480
00:20:07,206 --> 00:20:08,332
- [Karla] Oh?
- Hmm?

481
00:20:08,415 --> 00:20:09,666
She beats me to it!

482
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:13,587
[mischievous music playing]

483
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:16,089
They said kids are not allowed.

484
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:21,720
But why are there so many kids
going into the house?

485
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:23,138
[kids chattering]

486
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:25,807
Because it is the birthday
of the child who lives here.

487
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:28,685
Brother Atoy said kids are not allowed

488
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:30,562
because we are not invited.

489
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:33,523
That is why Sister Ame is in costume?

490
00:20:33,607 --> 00:20:35,525
[gentle music playing]

491
00:20:35,609 --> 00:20:38,737
Is a birthday party fun?

492
00:20:38,820 --> 00:20:41,573
I have never joined
parties like that before.

493
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:42,741
Hmm?

494
00:20:42,824 --> 00:20:45,327
You have not experienced a birthday party?

495
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:50,249
There is nothing like that
in the orphanage.

496
00:20:51,124 --> 00:20:52,417
Oh, poor you.

497
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:56,255
Oh, no! Do not continue those thoughts!

498
00:20:56,338 --> 00:20:58,090
It will only be for a moment.

499
00:20:58,173 --> 00:21:00,926
I will just let the child
experience a birthday party.

500
00:21:01,009 --> 00:21:02,261
Do what you want!

501
00:21:02,344 --> 00:21:04,972
But I am out of there
if you are seen by Brother Atoy!

502
00:21:05,055 --> 00:21:06,765
You will really take me with you?

503
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:11,019
Yeah, you are actually kind, Sis Tonet!

504
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:12,646
Mm! [smooches]

505
00:21:12,729 --> 00:21:13,647
Mm!

506
00:21:13,730 --> 00:21:15,607
Thank you!

507
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:18,277
Hey, hey, hey!

508
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:20,112
What are you doing here?!

509
00:21:20,195 --> 00:21:21,071
- [cock crowing]
- Who are you?

510
00:21:21,154 --> 00:21:22,572
Me? [chuckles]

511
00:21:22,656 --> 00:21:23,865
I am the clown at the party!

512
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:25,325
[chuckles] Hmm.

513
00:21:25,826 --> 00:21:27,202
Why did you come here?

514
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:28,287
And let go of that!

515
00:21:28,370 --> 00:21:30,122
That is worth more than your life!

516
00:21:31,957 --> 00:21:33,500
That is what I heard.

517
00:21:33,583 --> 00:21:34,918
What did you say?

518
00:21:35,002 --> 00:21:37,838
[suspenseful music playing]

519
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:39,548
Just a moment.

520
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:45,470
[grunting]

521
00:21:51,226 --> 00:21:52,227
[in English] Good night.

522
00:21:54,646 --> 00:21:58,066
Actually, I am even better than Tomtom.

523
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:00,068
He should be my assistant. Right?

524
00:22:00,152 --> 00:22:02,779
[kids cheering]

525
00:22:02,863 --> 00:22:04,323
Okay, wait a bit!

526
00:22:04,906 --> 00:22:06,742
[whimsical music playing]

527
00:22:06,825 --> 00:22:08,618
[in English] Ready for my magic trick?

528
00:22:08,702 --> 00:22:10,954
[kids cheering]

529
00:22:14,207 --> 00:22:15,042
‪Oh!

530
00:22:18,170 --> 00:22:21,214
- Mm!
- [kids cheering]

531
00:22:21,298 --> 00:22:23,550
[in English] I have another one.

532
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:31,391
[in English] Blow.

533
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:35,854
[huffs]

534
00:22:35,937 --> 00:22:38,065
[kids cheering]

535
00:22:38,148 --> 00:22:42,486
[kids applauding]

536
00:22:43,695 --> 00:22:46,656
More! I want juggling next!

537
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:51,119
Ah, more, juggling?
Okay, kids, your wish is my command!

538
00:22:51,203 --> 00:22:55,874
[kids cheering]

539
00:22:57,793 --> 00:22:59,252
Yes!

540
00:22:59,336 --> 00:23:02,631
Good thing I did
extra work at the fair before.

541
00:23:03,507 --> 00:23:06,718
[kids cheering]

542
00:23:06,802 --> 00:23:08,053
[whimsical music continues]

543
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:16,770
[funky music playing]

544
00:23:17,437 --> 00:23:23,777
[intense music playing]

545
00:23:24,486 --> 00:23:25,904
- [kids] Hi!
- [kids cheering]

546
00:23:25,987 --> 00:23:26,905
Did you get the rooster?

547
00:23:26,988 --> 00:23:31,576
[in English] I want Draco back,
and I want that man’s head!

548
00:23:31,660 --> 00:23:32,828
- [Ame] Oh!
- [man] Where are you going?

549
00:23:32,911 --> 00:23:33,787
- [thudding]
- [Tonet shrieks]

550
00:23:33,870 --> 00:23:34,871
- [thudding]
- [grunting]

551
00:23:34,955 --> 00:23:36,498
There is something illegal
that Atoy is doing.

552
00:23:36,581 --> 00:23:38,250
What kind of illegal thing is that, Boss?

553
00:23:38,333 --> 00:23:39,918
We need to find out.

554
00:23:40,001 --> 00:23:41,294
[Dmitri, in English] I am Dmitri.

555
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:42,337
[in English] And you are?

556
00:23:42,420 --> 00:23:43,964
[in English] I get it. No name.

557
00:23:44,047 --> 00:23:46,341
Were you not with
that acquaintance of yours

558
00:23:46,424 --> 00:23:49,678
who knows a contact who is a tracker?

559
00:23:49,761 --> 00:23:50,720
[in English] Why are you asking?

560
00:23:50,804 --> 00:23:52,556
[Audrey, in English] <i>I want to meet him.</i>

561
00:23:52,639 --> 00:23:55,767
UP NEXT
